@dev Return the current threshold set by the Governance multisig contract
 @return uint256 threshold

addTreasure(string,address,address).details: Used to add new Treasure assets (this method can only be called from the Multisig contract)   - Events:    - event AddTreasure(string treasureType,address producerContract,address produceDataContract);

params._producer: Management contract address corresponding to the asset's producer
params._productionData: Management contract address corresponding to the asset's production data

fmThreshold().details: Return the current threshold set by the Governance multisig contract

getTreasureByKind(string).details: Used to query the contract address corresponding to the asset type of Treasure

returns._1: address Production data management contract address

initialize(address,address,address,addre.details: Used for the initialization of the Governance contract

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
